<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
   Do the details interest you as much as the big picture? As an analyst in our Research group, you&#39;ll work with both as you help to cover large and small companies in a specific industry or an industry sector. You will gather, analyze, and interpret financial data but always in a broader context so you can provide not just information, but insight as well. That&#39;s how you add value. 
</p>
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Equity Research</H3>
<p class="bac">
Provides institutional and retail clients with in-depth research analysis on more than 20 industries and conducts fundamental analysis on more than 2,600 companies. 
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>  
<p class="bac">
   As an associate within Global Research, you will: 
</p>
<ul class="bac">	
	<li>Build relationships, knowledge and experience that will open doors to a wide range of future options and opportunities </li>	
	<li>Discover unlimited opportunities to challenge yourself and grow professionally </li>	
	<li>Engage in fundamental research activities with instructions from managers and colleagues who have experience and expertise in their respective areas</li>	
	<li>Develop an internal and external network of internal professionals and clients</li>	
	<li>Contribute and initiate leading edge, non-consensus, market moving research products and reports on corporate, sectors and markets </li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications:</h2>
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Education</H3>
<ul class="bac">	
	<li>MBA or other graduate degree from a top-tier school </li>	
	<li>A record of superior academic achievement </li>
</ul>
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Experience</H3>
<ul class="bac">	
	<li>Minimum 3 years work experience preferred </li>	
	<li>Prior experience in financial services helpful </li>
</ul>
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Skills and abilities </H3>
<ul class="bac">	
	<li>Strong analytical skills </li>	
	<li>Excellent presentation skills </li>	
	<li>Advanced written and oral communication skills </li>	
	<li>Accounting and quantitative skills </li>	
	<li>Well developed judgment and business sense </li>	
	<li>Strong interpersonal skills </li>
</ul>
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Personal traits</H3>
<ul class="bac">	
	<li>A passionate interest in the financial markets </li>	
	<li>High degree of self-motivation and initiative </li>	
	<li>Entrepreneurial drive with commercial acumen </li>	
	<li>Attentive to details </li>	
	<li>Team player </li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Training:</h2>
<p class="bac">
   Full-time associates are hired upon completion of their graduate degree. Your career as an associate begins with a formal training program followed by placement in one of our industry sector, country coverage, strategy, or economic teams. 
</p>
<p class="bac">
   The training program takes place in New York for all associates globally, and is considered one of the best in the industry. Instruction is provided by internal professionals and leading business school professors. 
</p>
<p class="bac">
The formal training program includes:  
</p>
<ul class="bac">	
	<li>A firm wide orientation program to introduce you to the bank </li>	
	<li>An overview of the financial markets and essential business skills </li>	
	<li>An intensive training program customized for associates that prepares you for your placement </li>	
	<li>A thorough review of legal and compliance issues </li>	
	<li>Instruction on Research templates and other technical training </li>	
	<li>Preparation for licensing and accreditation exams, where required</li>
</ul>

